      </p>
      <p>
        I am also part of a co-ed kickball team in Manhattan called "The Full Monty".  We play kickball and then flip cup on Thursdays.  We are, bar none, the best kickball team in all of Manhattan or so I hear.
      </p>
      <p>
    I also enjoy doing some creative writing in my free time when I am alone and have not much else to do. Usually this involves settling upon some random, but interesting or provocative prompt and going with it, wherever that may lead. Writing a novel is definitely something I want to do someday even if no one reads it. We’ll see.  I also enjoy writing satirical pieces from time to time, usually politically centered.
      </p>
      <p>
    I am also fulfilling my long delayed goal of picking up a musical instrument. I continuously played the guitar for like 3 months straight before being swamped by grad school. I am picking that up again and doing guitar classes in the city.  My goal is to become a mediocre guitar player and play Justin Bieber acoustic covers as part of a hip new band called "Bushwick Bop" or something.
      </p>
      <p>
